{
  "texts": [
    "The tumor is characterized by the uncontrolled growth of abnormal cells, invasion of adjacent parts of the body beyond normal boundaries, or metastasis to other organs, ultimately leading to death (1).",
    "According to the World Health Organization, malignant tumors have become one of the major threats to human health (2).",
    "Every year, millions of people die from cancer, with lung cancer, colorectal cancer, liver cancer, breast cancer, and cervical cancer being the most common types (3).",
    "During the development and progression of tumors, tumor cells are exposed to harsh conditions (4).",
    "To survive and sustain growth, cells must adapt to the environment."
  ]
}